<title>BRAZIL: Sao Paulo firms sack 4,278 workers in June.</title>
<headline>Sao Paulo firms sack 4,278 workers in June.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Private firms in Sao Paulo state laid off 4,278 employees in June, against 557 workers hired in May, Sao Paulo State Industries Federation (Fiesp) said in a statement.</p>
<p>Last month, seventeen out of the 47 sectors included in the survey sacked personnel, 22 hired new people and eight maintained their staff unchanged, it said.</p>
<p>In the last 12 months, Sao Paulo firms have sacked 104,158 workers, or 5,31 percent of Sao Paulo's industrial workforce.</p>
<p>So far this year, Sao Paulo industries have laid off 40,576 workers, or 2,16 percent of the Sao Paulo's industrial workforce, it added.</p>
<p>((-- Alexandre Caverni, Sao Paulo newsroom, 55 11 2485418))</p>
